social_posts.post_text: Ahead of my 6th full distance Ironman this Sunday, I want to thank my parents for traveling literally all over the world this year to help me out at these races! 😊🫶🏼 It’s been said time and time again - triathlon is technically an individual sport, but it ultimately takes a team of people in your corner to get to these start lines healthy and fit! 😊 I’m grateful for parents that love this sport as much as me do; and have time to come to these in places like Australia now that they both are retired! 😅😹🫶🏼 #family #love #noelsoul #westernaustralia @ironmanoceania 🇦🇺🦘

My last day in Nairobi before officially getting this run camp started! I am off to a town called Iten up in the mountains at 10,000 feet elevation to begin a 3 week run camp! 🏃🏼‍♂️ I will take a prop plane 🛫 to Kisamu and then a 3 hour road trip to Iten. It’s all dirt roads and the fastest runners in the world are produced there! 😍  My hotel was amazing here in the city and I couldn’t recommend it more! 😍 @villarosakempinski !! 😍 What an amazing stay! 🥰
Making new friends is my favorite hobby 😍🥹🥰 #kenya #exploremore

Kenya Run Camp DAY 1! 🇰🇪🏃🏼‍♂️. Today we got our bearings around the village of Iten! 👀 It’s all dirt roads and literally every single person you pass waves and says hi! I feel like I met half the town this morning. 😹😍 Iten is also called ‘home of champions’. Runners from all over the world descend to this rural town to run the hills and absorb the world’s best runners atmosphere and vibes. Today I did a 6 mile run and did 2 TT dances with two different groups of locals! One lady wanted me to take her to the US with her because she wants to live there. I told her yes!!! 😀 Than me, @chlorichx and @marcscott21 went to the gym! The buildings have no air conditioning here and it’s hot and at 8000 feet elevation. 😅 No wonder these people are the fittest people on earth! 😍 Time to get running! 😍
POV: you wake up for a morning run in Kenya! 😍🥹 Thanks so much @iten_accommodation - we are loving it so much! 😍
My taxi to the gym was fun today! 😎🤩🛵 Welcome to Iten, home if champions! 🤩 I’m not one yet, but maybe one day! 😄
Meet Joan ☺️
Taxi service in here in Iten is super convenient! (yes I should be wearing a helmet they don’t have any tho) 😟

I had a complete rest today because i felt super sick and nauseous all day. Like so bad 😟😭! But than @chlorichx got me out of bed for an excursion to the local shops and we bought lollipops for all the local children near the compound! 🥹 and it still was a good day. Progress is never linear huh!??😣
When the local kids know you have lollipops! 😅 #kenya #fun

This is the hardest running I’ve ever done, which I excepted to some extent…But wow! talk about feeling out of shape! 😅 8000 to 9000 feet elevation, all dirt roads and hills. The UV index is 11, meaning it only takes 11 minutes to burn in the sun! ☀️ There’s no hope for anyone else in the world beating the Kenyans at long distance running. 😂They grow up their entire lives doing this. It’s amazing to see! There’s a reason they are the best! 😻🫶🏼 Besides being sick, and not doing as much running as I had hoped thus far…I feel like I am becoming a better athlete just by being here! 😊🫡🏃🏼‍♂️ - 📸 - @chlorichx ❤️
Everything the light touches 🌅🫡 - 📸 - @chlorichx 😍

Me: “Chloe did you feel good on your run?” 😀 Chloe: “No not at all. Did you feel good on yours?” - Me: “not in the slightest bit” 🤣 - Me and my training partner @chlorichx are absolutely struggling out here. 😵‍💫😹🫠😵‍💫 But we trying every day! 😍🏝️🧉😁
Our afternoon core routine overlooking the valley in the sun!! ☀️🌞🌅

A $12 helmet, an $8 per day rental mountain bike with barely functioning brakes, a ton of sunscreen, and one single road out of town! 😍 Running is cool and all, but there is absolutely no better way to see a place than by bike! 🤩😁 I’ve been craving to bike since I got here and the stars aligned yesterday. 🥹 3 hours solo on a mountain bike through the Kenyan country side. 🇰🇪✨🐄🐮🐑🦃 Where the air is thin, the sun is STRONG, and the coke is 10 cents per liter. 😊
Very hard day at the famous Kipchoge Stadium being lapped by 2:05 marathoners! 😁 WHAT AN EXPERIENCE! 😍🤩
Fruity day!!! 😍 Smoothie shack with Chloe and Marc! 😍😄
I lasted literally 2 minutes before they began their FARTLEKs and I was proud of that! 🤠
This cow speaks Swahili 😍
My biggest run week in years! 62 miles for the week at 8000 feet elevation! 😌😍 Sunny, muddy, dusty, out of breath, and loving it! 🥰😍 - 📸 @jackrowe._
Fresh watermelon at the track! 😍

At the dirt track a few miles down the road, this kid asked if he could pace me on my workout with the rental bike I road to it. I said absolutely! But the back tire is flat. He didn’t care and did it anyways 😆🚴🏼‍♂️🏃🏼‍♂️ made the workout go so much faster! 😁 @kimesh_pictures 📸
Nearly a month now with the best training partner in the whole world @chlorichx taking on the dirt roads and altitude of Iten together! 😍🤩 - 📸 @kimesh_pictures 🌴

LISTEN UP! 🗣️ JUST START RUNNING! It doesn’t have to be complicated!!! I have to say my two cents on this because I’m so sick of seeing it everywhere and it’s driving me crazy! 😭 Do NOT overthink running!! 😫😵‍💫✋🏼 You don’t need to worry about all these terms that keep getting flung around: ‘cadence, heart rate, form, army carriage, knee drive, heal strike,” just stop!!! ✋🏼🛑🥸!!! That’s for later in the process, if ever! Your body will find its natural flow state when you start running. It’s one of the most natural things a human being can do. If you haven’t read it yet, read the book ‘Born To Run’ by Christopher McDougall! We evolved to run long distances, LONG LONG before any sort of pacing, metrics, etc. 🥸 Too MUCH thinking can stop you from starting in my opinion. Put on some shoes and get out the door. Your heart ❤️ lungs 🫁 and feet 👣 will know what to do. 😚😍

It’s my dad telling me to move out of the way…😅 Little story about what happened here: on Thursday before the race I went to a local bike shop in Lake Placid to have them adjust my seat properly since I didn’t have a torque wrench. I guess that they didn’t secure it properly. 😟 At mile 10 of the bike I remember hearing a big cracking sound. VERY NOTICEABLE. 🙀 I initially thought  it was my seat post going down. I looked to see if the line was still in the right place and it was! So I forgot about it and thought nothing more of it….UNTIL! Around mile 100 of the bike I could NOT figure out why I was in excruciating pain. 😹💀 Arms, back, shoulders, neck. It felt like I had been holding a plank for 4 hours now. 🫨😵‍💫 I was thinking maybe I swam too hard or pulled something in the swim!?? I couldn’t understand what was going on! 😓 With twelve miles left I finally got off to stretch, and than I saw it!! 🙀 I had been riding with my bike seat sloped down for 102 miles now. 😅 I was actually very relieved to find out it was the bike seat and it wasn’t just me being completely out of shape. Because for four hours I was convinced I just suck. 🤣🤷🏼‍♂️🧍🏼‍♂️😥 As I pulled into the end of the bike I stopped and asked my dad to take a pic of the saddle real quick because I wanted to look at it closer and I didn’t know when I’d get my bike back. This is that clip. 😅 All good now. I talked to my @cyclologic family and they are helping me fix it to make sure this never happens again. ONE BIG LESSON: don’t mess with your saddle if it’s fine. 😅
